  "text": "Alternatively, small vessel endothelial function can be measured by using the skin circulation as a surrogate marker of generalised microvascular endothelial function. In this process, vasoactive chemicals (e.g. acetylcholine (endothelium-dependent) and sodium nitroprusside (endothelium-independent)) can be delivered transdermally to the skin microvessels using a small electric current (iontophoresis). The subsequent microvascular response can be measured by laser Doppler imaging, which measures perfusion in the top 1·0-1·5 mm of skin. Although the prognostic value of small vessel endothelial function has yet to be demonstrated, changes in the microcirculation have been shown to parallel changes in the macrocirculation [CITATION_1] .",
